o key companies and institutions participants are immersed in an intensive experience with accomplished peers from around the world at stanford university in the heart of silicon valley participants the sprie executive education program is designed for an elite group of leaders who play key roles for development within their region as well as for their region internationally sprie at stanford university work with partners to select delegations from developed and emerging high technology regions including but not limited to regions in asia north america latin america and europe contact program coordinator stanford program on regions of innovation and entrepreneurship sprie knight management center stanford university 655 knight way stanford ca 94305 7298 usa phone 1.650 725.1885 fax 1.650 721.2198 sprie stanford stanford edu search sprie more information marguerite gong hancock associate director sprie william f miller herbert hoover professor of public and private management emeritus professor of computer science emeritus and former provost stanford university and faculty co director sprie yan mei sprie program coordinator support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds stanford program on regions of innovation and entrepreneurship stanford graduate school of business knight management center mcclelland bldg 655 knight way stanford ca 94305 7298 tel 650 725 1885 fax 650 725 2198 mail code 7298
